JA  - 2022 IEEE 8th International Conference on Computer and Communications (ICCC)
Y1  - 9-12 Dec. 2022
AB  - We make a comparison among six movement methods which were previously proposed for cooperative work of carrying an object between remote robot systems with force feedback. In each system, a user remotely controls a robot by using a haptic interface device while monitoring how the robot moves. The six methods are different from each other in terms of how to move one robot; for example, in one method, a human instead of the robot moves the object. By experiment, we examine the influence of the movement velocity of the object on the force applied to the object. As a result, we demonstrate that as the movement velocity increases, the robot becomes more largely inferior to the human.
ER  - 

